The paper deals with efficient algorithms for matrix computations, specifically for sparse matrices that can be multiplied by a vector using softO(n) field operations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of block projections, which are commonly used in Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Scientific Computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper discusses the computation of the inverse of a matrix and the certification of its rank, which are topics that fall under the sub-category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
